'''世界厕所日'''（{{lang-en|World Toilet Day}}）是[[联合国|联合国]]正式{{le|小型世俗纪念日列表|List of minor secular observances|国际纪念日}}，旨在启发激烈采取行动应对全球[[卫生设施|卫生设施]]危机<ref name=":7">{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldtoiletday.info/|title=What is World Toilet Day?|website=World Toilet Day|access-date=2017-11-16|archive-date=2017-11-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115190902/http://www.worldtoiletday.info/|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{cite web|url=https://www.un.org/millenniumgoals/pdf/DSG%20sanitation%20two-pager%20FINAL.pdf|title=Call to action on UN website|date=|website=|publisher=|accessdate=2014-10-19|archive-date=2015-06-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150601174853/http://www.un.org/millenniumgoals/pdf/DSG%20sanitation%20two-pager%20FINAL.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。目前全球有42亿人过着没有{{le|已改善卫生设施|Improved sanitation|可管理安全卫生设施}}的生活，约6.73亿人还在[[露天排便|露天排便]]<ref name="JMP2017">{{cite book |author1=UNICEF |author2=World Health Organization |title=Progress on household drinking water, sanitation and hygiene 2000-2017: Special focus on inequalities |date=2019 |isbn=978-92-415-1623-5 |publisher=United Nations Children’s Fund |location=Geneva, Switzerland |url=https://www.who.int/water_sanitation_health/publications/jmp-report-2019/en/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200825160347/https://www.who.int/water_sanitation_health/publications/jmp-report-2019/en/ |archivedate=2020-08-25 |access-date=2020-08-25 |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{rp|74}}。因此联合国提出{{tsl|en|Sustainable Development Goal 6|可持续发展目标第6号}}，目标实现卫生设施全球覆盖，消除露天排便陋习<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.un.org/sustainabledevelopment/water-and-sanitation/|title=Goal 6: Ensure access to water and sanitation for all|website=United Nations|access-date=2017-11-18|archive-date=2015-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151127115032/http://www.un.org/sustainabledevelopment/water-and-sanitation/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，世界厕所日便是顺应这一目标而举行。

2013年，[[联合国大会|联合国大会]]通过新加坡将世界厕所日列为联合国官方节日的决议<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.un.org/en/events/toiletday/background.shtml|title=World Toilet Day 19 November - Background|website=United Nations|access-date=2017-11-30|archive-date=2017-12-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210164039/http://www.un.org/en/events/toiletday/background.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":12">{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/singapores-first-un-resolution-adopted-now-every-nov-19-is-world-toilet-day|title=Singapore's first UN resolution adopted; now, every Nov 19 is World Toilet Day|last=Chan|first=Robin|date=2013-07-24|website=The Straits Times|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116173018/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/singapores-first-un-resolution-adopted-now-every-nov-19-is-world-toilet-day|archive-date=2019-11-16|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>。在此之前，该节日一直是2001年成立的新加坡非政府组织[[世界厕所组织|世界厕所组织]]举行的非官方节日。

[[聯合國水資源組織|聯合國水資源組織]]是世界厕所日的组织方，负责世界厕所日网站的维护，并为每年的活动选择特定主主题。2019年的主题“不落下任何一个人”为[[可持续发展目标|可持续发展目标]]的中心主题。前几年的主题涵盖{{le|基于自然的解决方案|nature-based solutions}}、[[废水|废水]]、厕所与就业及厕所与[[营养|营养]]<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":8" /><ref name=":9">{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldtoiletday.info/2015/about/|title=World Toilet Day Website - About (2015)|access-date=2018-10-12|archive-date=2018-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013014317/http://www.worldtoiletday.info/2015/about/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。节日当天会有形式多样的宣传活动，由[[聯合國大會觀察員列表|联合国观察员]]、国际组织、地方[[非政府组织|公民社会组织]]及{{tsl|en|raising awareness|提高意识}}启发行动的志愿者组织。

世界厕所日的主要是[[马桶|马桶]]。功能齐全的厕所对[[公共卫生|公共卫生]]、[[尊严|个人尊严]]及个人安全（尤其是女性）有正面影响，因此非常重要<ref name="autogenerated3" />。而不能安全处理粪便的卫生设施系统会导致疾病传播<ref name="JMP2017" />，例如[[霍亂|霍亂]]、[[腹瀉|腹瀉]]、[[伤寒|伤寒]]、[[痢疾|痢疾]]和[[血吸虫病|血吸虫病]]等严重{{tsl|en|soil-transmitted helminthiasis|土壤传播蠕虫病}}和{{tsl|en|waterborne diseases|水源性疾病}}。

==背景==
[[File:Child_in_open_sewer_in_Nigeria_(3150664698).jpg|thumb]]Gege贫民窟的运河里随地便溺。]]
目前全球有42亿人过着没有{{le|已改善卫生设施|Improved sanitation|可管理安全卫生设施}}的生活，约6.73亿人还在[[露天排便|露天排便]]<ref name="JMP2017" />{{rp|74}}。露天排便对妇女及女孩来说尤为艰难。妇女倾向于用黑暗掩护她们在露天排便时的隐私，但夜晚单独在外边这么做会让她们面临被袭击的风险<ref name="autogenerated3">{{cite web|last1=Cavill|first1=Sue|title=Violence, gender and WASH: A practitioner's toolkit: Making Water, Sanitation and hygiene safer through improved programming and services|url=http://violence-wash.lboro.ac.uk/|publisher=WaterAid, SHARE Research Consortium|access-date=2015-10-07|archive-date=2015-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151004081037/http://violence-wash.lboro.ac.uk/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite journal|last1=Lennon|first1=Shirley|title=Fear and anger: Perceptions of risks related to sexual violence against women linked to water and sanitation in Delhi, India|journal=SHARE (Sanitation and Hygiene Applied Research for Equity) and WaterAid, UK|date=November 2011|url=http://www.susana.org/en/resources/library/details/1758|access-date=2015-10-07|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924112250/http://www.susana.org/en/resources/library/details/1758|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

据估计，2015年的[[腹泻|腹泻]]病例中，有58%的病因为用水不安全、卫生设施条件恶劣及卫生习惯差（例如[[洗手|洗手]]不恰当）<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Burden of disease from inadequate water, sanitation and hygiene in low- and middle-income settings: a retrospective analysis of data from 145 countries|date=2014|journal=Tropical Medicine|volume=19|issue=8|pages=894–905|doi=10.1111/tmi.12329|pmid=24779548|pmc=4255749|last1=Prüss-Ustün|first1=Annette|last2=Bartram|first2=Jamie|last3=Clasen|first3=Thomas|last4=Colford|first4=John M.|last5=Cumming|first5=Oliver|last6=Curtis|first6=Valerie|last7=Bonjour|first7=Sophie|last8=Dangour|first8=Alan D.|last9=De France|first9=Jennifer|last10=Fewtrell|first10=Lorna|last11=Freeman|first11=Matthew C.|last12=Gordon|first12=Bruce|last13=Hunter|first13=Paul R.|last14=Johnston|first14=Richard B.|last15=Mathers|first15=Colin|last16=Mäusezahl|first16=Daniel|last17=Medlicott|first17=Kate|last18=Neira|first18=Maria|last19=Stocks|first19=Meredith|last20=Wolf|first20=Jennyfer|last21=Cairncross|first21=Sandy}}</ref>。每年50万年龄在5岁以下的儿童死于上述原因的腹泻<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|title=UNICEF: Ending Child Deaths from Pneumonia and Diarrhoea|date=2015|url=https://data.unicef.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Pneumonia_Diarrhoea_brochure.pdf|website=UNICEF|format=PDF|accessdate=2017-03-20|archive-date=2017-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320233347/https://data.unicef.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Pneumonia_Diarrhoea_brochure.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。提供安全设施预计可将儿童罹患腹泻的几率降低至7到17%，将5岁以下儿童的死亡率降至5到20%<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Gunther|first1=Isabel|last2=Fink|first2=Gunther|date=April 2010|title=Water, Sanitation and Children's Health Evidence from 172 DHS Surveys|url=https://sanitationupdates.files.wordpress.com/2010/05/worldbank-dhs2010.pdf|journal=The World Bank Development Economics Prospects Group|issue=5275|accessdate=2015-10-07|archive-date=2015-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119224626/https://sanitationupdates.files.wordpress.com/2010/05/worldbank-dhs2010.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[享有饮水和卫生设施的人权|饮水及卫生设施权]]已于2010年7月18日被[[联合国大会|联合国大会]]认定为[[人权|人权]]。[[卫生设施|卫生设施]]（厕所）的缺乏会影响[[公共卫生|公共卫生]]、[[尊严|尊严]]及安全.<ref name="autogenerated3" />。厕所的缺乏会导致{{le|人类粪便|human feces}}直接传播诸如[[腹泻|腹泻]]、[[血吸虫病|血吸虫病]]等{{tsl|en|soil-transmitted helminthiasis|土壤传播蠕虫病}}，或造成儿童{{le|发育迟缓|stunted growth}}。

{{tsl|en|Sustainable Development Goal 6|可持续发展目标第6号}}旨在实现卫生设施全覆盖<ref name="JMP2017" />。

